<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">scp-4460</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">scp-4460</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>So, not exactly sure where on Earth I got this idea. All I know know is that I hate the article and it is bad.<br />
Yeah that's it</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">scp-4944</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">scp-4944</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I initially got the idea while in the car with my mom. She mentioned that our coffee machine sounds like a fog horn while its heating up. The idea instantly popped into my head: &quot;A coffee machine that if you press a certain button, it will turn into a cargo ship&quot;</p>
<p>That obviously isn't what happened, though.<br />
I honestly don't even know how I got the idea that turned out to be the final product. All I knew was that I was taking my coffee machine out into my back yard, barefoot, right after it snowed. Yeah, it was cold.</p>
<p>After some crooping and cropping, I got all the text to sound right in my head.</p>
<p>Apparently people really like this scip. It's currently my most upvoted article, and even got into an episode of SCP Cafè, which is a level of loft I will never reach again.</p>
<p>All in all, I still like this article.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">scp-2704</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">scp-2704</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>&quot;Hey there's a series III article open&quot;<br />
<em>eeeheuh?</em></p>
<p>so yeah.</p>
<p>Again, not real sure where this concept came from.</p>
<p>After I had finished writing the whole scip, (2 days after realizing that there was a series III article open) I decided to check if the slot was still open, which is <em>was.</em></p>
<p>It wasn't real well received, which I can see. I decided to delete a major plot point in the article just because I was stretching the whole thing too thin.</p>
</div>
</div>
